## FAQ

### What is the best AI chatbot for writing?
Claude, particularly the Claude Opus 4.6 and Claude Mythos models, is widely considered the best chatbot for long-form writing. It naturally balances tone, context, and structural flow without sounding overly robotic or unnatural.

### Can these chatbots write and debug code?
Yes. ChatGPT (using GPT-4.1) and Claude both feature exceptional coding capabilities. They can identify complex bugs, generate functional scripts, and even help architect robust software systems across multiple programming languages.

### Which AI chatbot is best for verifiable research?
Perplexity AI is specifically designed for research. Because it builds live citations and source links directly into every response, users can easily fact-check the information, ensuring higher accuracy than standard generative platforms.

### Are off-the-shelf chatbots secure for enterprise data?
Enterprise editions of Copilot and Gemini feature strong enterprise governance, but using consumer versions of any chatbot carries data privacy risks. For businesses wanting to secure their proprietary data, deploying a customized ecosystem via a platform like Chatzy AI is highly recommended.

### How does a custom AI agent differ from ChatGPT?
While ChatGPT functions as a general knowledge assistant, a custom AI agent built on a platform like Chatzy AI is trained strictly on your specific company documents, Zendesk tickets, and website. It focuses entirely on your business workflows and plugs directly into your customer-facing communication channels.

